# Script version history

When editing any tracked script or profile file, add a new **top** history line (newest first). Do not edit older lines.

## Shell scripts (`*.sh`, `install.sh`, `_doit.sh`)

Immediately after the shebang:

```bash
# YYYY.MM.DD - v. MAJOR.MINOR - brief what changed
```

Bump patch/minor from the current top entry. Keep one short line.

## Profile files (`bashrc`, `bash_profile`)

At file top (no shebang):

```bash
# v. MAJOR.MINOR- YYYY.MM.DD - brief what changed
```

When `bashrc` or `bash_profile` changes, also add a matching top line to `.pgm-bundle-version` (bundle release note).

## After changes

Commit and push to `master` unless the user says otherwise.
